entry.title: [AboutThisSite] Fix heap use after free & links opening on wrong window
entry.content:
The ATS was using BrowserView to deal with the events of the

ATSSidePanel WebContents, i.e. it redirects to the browser clicks on

links and mouse events on the SidePanel's diner webpage. However, the

BrowserView associated with a tab can change if a tab is moved to

another window.



In this CL, we make ATSSidePanel depend directly on the tab's

WebContents instead of the BrowserView associated with the tab's

WebContents at the creation moment of the ATSSidePanel. The tab's web

contents will remain the same for the lifetime of the ATSSidePanelView

and we can fetch the correct BrowserView when an event related to the

side panel's WebContents occurs.

entry.content:
Before this change, on macOS, if an incognito window was opened as the

frontmost window, a url from other app (e.g. Mail app) was opened on the

incognito window. The reason behind this erroneous behavior was that

the passed profile was an incognito profile.



This change fixes `OpenUrlsInBrowserWithProfile` to prefer a regular

(non-incognito) profile.

entry.title: Add local AudioBuffer pool
entry.content:
This CL reduces memory allocation made from the Realtime Audio capture

thread, by pooling AudioBuffers and overwriting data instead.



We cannot completely get rid of memory allocation unfortunately, as

some will have to be made whenever there is a format change. We also

cannot pre-allocate AudioBuffers from the main thread, since we have

to wait until the audio format is received in the RT audio thread.



A quick capture test which pipes a microphone stream though

BreakoutBox and into WebAudio shows that we end up reusing a single

AudioBuffer.

entry.title: [Extensions c2s] Add 'policy installed' entry in context menu
entry.content:
Adds a new POLICY_INSTALLED entry in the context menu when extension is

required by policy.



Previously we had UNINSTALL entry cover both "uninstall" and

"installed by admin", which was visible and enabled dependent on the

situation. Since the context menu under feature

kExtensionsMenuAccessControl moves the "install by admin" to another place (page access submenu, or right after page access item) it's

better to separate the entry since they are different enough. It also

makes checking the command if enabled, and running command easier.

entry.title: [Zucchini] Refactor BufferSource::Skip().
entry.content:
BufferSource::Skip() had two main uses:

1. Advance cursor by a known number of bytes.

2. Seek to an absolute offset of an image, e.g., via:

source = std::move(BufferSource(image).Skip(offset));

To support (2), Skip() returned ref to |*this| for chaining.



In retrospect, (2) was a kludge to get BufferSource::Seek(), which in

turn was absent because BufferView is implemented as a "shrinking range"

(2 fields) instead of a "fixed range with cursor" (3 fields).



This CL makes some simple cleanup to Skip() by doing the following:

* Restrict Skip() to (1) by changing its return type to bool to indicate

whether the skip would have exceeded bound.

* Do (2) a different way: Add new BufferSource CTOR that takes an offset

param, so the above usage becomes:

source = BufferSource(image, offset);

* Down-cast BufferSource CTOR that takes ConstBufferView: Change to take

const ref instead of value, for consistency.

* Update callers.

* Update BufferSourceTest.Skip and other tests that use Skip().

* Add BufferSourceTest.{CtorWithOffset, SkipAcrossEnd}.
